tags.name: csv-render
tags.description:
`csv-render`
`Remote render a CSV file in place as an accessible table.`

Attributes:

  * `data-source` {`string`} - Location of the CSV file.

  * `caption` {`string`} - Caption for the table to improve accessibility and readability.

  * `summary` {`string`} - Summary to improve accessibility for screen readers.

  * `color` {`string`} - Color class work to apply

  * `table` {`any[]`} - Table busted out as an array.

  * `tableHeadings` {`any[]`} - Headings from the first row of the csv

  * `table-data` {`string`} - Raw data pulled in from the csv file.

  * `accent-color` {`string`} - a selected accent-"color": grey, red, pink, purple, etc.

  * `dark` {`boolean`} - make the default theme dark?

  * `colors` - make the default theme dark?

Properties:

  * `dataSource` {`string`} - Location of the CSV file.

  * `caption` {`string`} - Caption for the table to improve accessibility and readability.

  * `summary` {`string`} - Summary to improve accessibility for screen readers.

  * `color` {`string`} - Color class work to apply

  * `table` {`any[]`} - Table busted out as an array.

  * `tableHeadings` {`any[]`} - Headings from the first row of the csv

  * `tableData` {`string`} - Raw data pulled in from the csv file.

  * `accentColor` {`string`} - a selected accent-"color": grey, red, pink, purple, etc.

  * `dark` {`boolean`} - make the default theme dark?

  * `__utils` - 

  * `colors` - make the default theme dark?
